summary: Okay I feel like I’m late to the game asking, but what kind of music are we hoping Taylor releases????? Or what kind of music do...
body:
Okay I feel like I’m late to the game asking, but what kind of music are we hoping Taylor releases????? Or what kind of music do you think this era will bring???

Personally I hope it is like a mixture of every album she’s done. The colors remind me of the fearless and debut era. Since we are going into summer soon, I think an album that is summery would be really cool!! The butterfly’s make me think that now this is a celebration of life and off to the next adventure!

blog.name: deepbluebuttaypaintedmegolden
blog.title: Sandra
blog.description: Taylor’s words got me through the toughest times. Forever a Swifty.

body:
Weird, but true.

Ever since @taylorswift put out her very first album, the concept always reflects my real life. Especially during the RED era. All too well will forever remind me of a specific event that broke me. The album had literally just dropped and I was listening to it for the very first time when THAT song came on. It was like she put every single thought and emotion I was having into words. THAT song helped me make sense of it all. Then we get to 1989 and between blank space, style, out of the woods, clean, wonderland and New Romantics it was my story in words all over again. Then we get to Reputation. I lost “friends” to a rumor. I trusted the wrong people. I felt comepetely broken and alone. And here comes Taylor Alison Swift to save me again. Then THE REP TOUR happens. I went both nights in Santa Clara and let me tell you, her words are so kind and so geniuine and both shows were just as different as they were the same. Proving to me what I already knew to be true. Those words that made up laugh and cry and the love she shows for everyone at every show is real. At this point in my life I’m really doing better than I ever was. TS7 is going to be pure magic. I’m in a really good place and the parallels are always there. I can already feel this album even without having heard it yet. I CANNOT WAIT.
